Author: Pasquini
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Sirin Labs is going through some trouble right now. A lot is at stake, the company could either continue down the path to possible insolvency or make a comeback and improve sales and development of the Finney. Honestly I believe Sirin Labs has everything it needs to survive and continue accomplishing great achievements beyond the Finney itself.  However the determining factor will come to the competency of the management. The team seems solid, I am worried about how seriously Moshe Hogeg is about Sirin Labs. He obviously wasn't determined in saving his other ICO projects that eventually failed despite raising substantial funds. His business practices seem very questionable and if Sirin Labs had a CEO with a proven track record and credibility, I wouldn't doubt the company for a second even with the recent 25% lay off of staff. Moshe Hogeg is my biggest concern about Sirin Labs. I don't want to be the one to doubt an ambitious entrepreneur as I love ambition and those who pursue great goals, but his history and reputation has been in question along with the question of the ethics of his business practices.  I hope Sirin Labs survives and continues to update the Finney. I currently own this innovative phone and love it. It would be sad for such a project to end at this time.

Author: sukhwindersingh
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The purpose of the strategic reinjection is to maintain a healthy ecosystem. Since the SRN token is a utility token, it's purpose is to be used. If we simply held every token that was used, the supply would quickly evaporate, and it would become more and more difficult for individuals to obtain the tokens needed to use the SRN functionality within the phone, and to purchase SIRIN LABS goods and services. We're leading the crypto revolution, in order to bridge the gap between the blockchain economy and the mass market, and that means we need to make the token widely available for anyone who wants to use that. Simultaniously, we recognize the impact on the token economy outside of our ecosystem, which is why we will be doing it strategically, to ensure we do not have an affect.

Author: tientien1
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The FINNEY’s cold-storage wallet will be designed to seamlessly interact between tokens and coins that are supported within the wallet. So first, the ADA token will be supported in the wallet. Next, we are creating a DApp store and providing developers with an SDK to significantly grow the number of DApps in existence. This partnership will bring ADA support and functionality to the DApp store, meaning that if you want to purchase an app from the DApp store, but you only have ADA stored in your wallet and since all transactions will need to be performed in SRN, you will be able to make that purchase in ADA. The wallet’s functionality will automatically and seamlessly exchange your ADA for SRN. Users will be prompted to approve a transaction for the appropriate amount of ADA, and then the phone will conduct the transaction in SRN.

Author: yassinebenouhoud
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Sirin OS, the software The Finney will run, will give users the full Android experience with the basic Google package. The phone will run Oreo (or whatever the latest version of Android is at the time of release). The Play Store and all apps within it will be available on The Finney. Sirin OS will enhance the security of the entire handset and the usability of cold wallets. Sirin is working closely with Google to make sure user experience stays the same and all apps work, including releasing the latest Android updates via firmware over-the-air (FOTA). Finney will let users have the experience that they’re used to along with an extension beyond the Android OS to ensure the blockchain and wallet security.

Author: BenNad
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Aside from purchasing the phone itself, SRN will be used as the currency within the SIRIN LABS ecosystem through the SIRIN OS. Additionally, any OEM using the SIRIN OS will be required to maintain the SRN as the currency.  So, simply put, for any phone running SIRIN OS, all blockchain transactions through the phone itself (e.g. the DApp store, or monetized phone resources through the secure P2P connections) will require use of the SRN.

Author: theone189
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Hello,  The Finney is scheduled to be released in H2 of this year. It is a deposit of 50 SRN required to pre-order a Finney. If you pre-order it in February  you will get a 10% discount on the price.   The price of the phone is set at the equivalent to ~$999USD, payable in SRN. When the phone is released, the price in SRN will be dictated by the exchange rate then, not now. You pay a pre-order deposit of 50 SRN.   When the phone is released, if 50SRN<$999USD, there will be a balance due. If 50 SRN>$999SRN, you will get a refund on the cost of the phone. (This is excluding taxes and shipping).   If you qualified for the 10% discount, use the rate of 50 SRN:$900USD.   The only way to preorder a Finney is following this Preorder link: https://sirinlabs.com/preorder.html   Once you complete this form you will get an email with the next steps to proceed with the payment.   There will be instructions in the email you will receive from preorder@sirinlabs.com once you complete the above steps.  Note: Please do not send the preorder deposit from an exchange wallet.  The preorder confirmation will be sent within 48 hrs business hours after sending the preorder deposit.   Thank you for being part of the Sirin Labs Community!

Author: kimamaxgreen
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Developers at Sirin Labs have created the most secure hand held device.  From Idea to Reality To function effectively in the mass market in the foreseeable future, companies will need to create tangible, working technologies for consumers to use.

Author: kimamaxgreen
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Currently, much of cryptospace lacks a product for mass consumer adoption. Companies state their blockchain tech is disruptive, or will disrupt a specific market, but they have not yet developed a truly working model or device for that purpose.  Notwithstanding, there is one company that appears to be a front runner in the race to mass market adoption, Sirin Labs.  Sirin Labs first gained public attention in December of 2017 by announcing its ICO, which sold roughly $160 million dollars worth of Sirin Lab Tokens (SRN) within hours of release.

Author: kimamaxgreen
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: What led to such demand? What does Sirin Labs do differently?  The answers to those questions, from our perspective, are clear:  Sirin Labs has developed partnerships with several of the worlds most revered technology companies, including Google, and is disrupting the very lucrative cell phone industry.

Author: kimamaxgreen
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: By way of blockchain technology, the developers at Sirin Labs have created the most secure hand held device our world has come to see. With the intricacies of blockchain and the various ingenious ideas added to the FINNEY phone, Sirin Labs is one of few blockchain companies to have an official working product, which should hit shelves in the next year.

Author: plantpeople89
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The charging of battery is one POC (proof of concept) that we did during the Alpha phase--and yes, it is working--but this use case is not important for the project. Let's look at the big picture and hope that it will be more clear:  What we are doing is extending the operating system to give any OEM (original equipment manufacturer) the ability to use our open source and implement it - what it gives the OEM is secure, P2P (peer to peer) communication, that will be separated from the operating system itself. We will also provide the developers an SDK (software development kit) so that they can implement any further ideas of secure P2P resource sharing.  We’d like to make data sharing, and other resource sharing, easier than it is now, and more secure. You will get data locally and securely through P2P communication instead of sharing passwords. Only apps developed and verified for the Sirin OS will be able to share resources, which also ensures your security. Please let us know what other resources you’d like to be able to share!

Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The easiest way I know that is the most secure is to use https://www.myetherwallet.com/ in conjunction with Metamask. There's no way around it. This way, you avoid sending your private keys to the site and also avoid sending them to a fake site accidently.  First you open metamask and then import your private keys and then start following the instructions at MEW for sending tokens.  MEW interacts with Metamask through API calls and signed messages so that MEW doesn't need to know your private keys.   If I help you with this, I wouldn't mind you click "merit", thanks!

Author: duocnguyen
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Sirin OS, the software The Finney will run, will give users the full Android experience with the basic Google package. The Play Store and all apps within it will be available on The Finney. Sirin OS will enhance security and the usability of cold wallets. Sirin is working closely with Google to make sure user experience stays the same and all apps work, including releasing the latest Android updates. Finney will let users have the experience that they’re used to along with an extension beyond the Android OS to ensure the blockchain and wallet security.  Sirin OS will not run on existing phones, and we will not be releasing the OS to individuals, only to companies. Sirin will work with the companies to ensure integration into the phones developed by OEMs (original equipment manufacturers).

Author: campion99
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Developers who use the SDK (software developer’s kit) will have Dapps available on the phone that will run seamlessly with Sirin OS and allow for the use of SRN token payment. SRN will be the center of the OS; everyone who wants to use an application in the OS will need to use SRN. We’ll do an automatic conversion to SRN during the purchase. This will be part of the developer’s kit and ensure that the user experience will be seamless. The end user will just use the application and not have to worry about trading the tokens. We are working on keeping the SDK simple.  We believe in open source and that community is important for the success of the Sirin OS. We also believe in Android. G1 was the first phone to implement Android OS;  Finney will be the first phone to implement the Sirin OS.  The main developing language is Java, but we’d like to hear from developers what additional languages they want supported.

Author: bulacarango
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The vision for SIRIN LABS has never been short term. The timeline outlined on our website and in the whitepaper was very clear that the SRN is a utility token, and not a security token. As such, the goal is to drive value to the SRN token through mass-market demand for SIRIN LABS products and services.  Currently, we are 5-11 months away from our projected release date. If you jumped onto the SIRIN LABS bandwagon to try and make a quick buck, you’ve misunderstood and perhaps shouldn’t be on the bandwagon at all. We are here to build a solid, reputable and long-lasting company, and that doesn’t happen overnight. I hope that this is something that interests you, and that you’re able to take this journey together with us.

Author: deort
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Incidentally, I just now saw a mention of BlockShield, which provides OS security. And I also saw the mention of SecureShield, but did not understand how this shell will work for applications. Can anyone explain?

Author: gavrosh
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The SecureShield ™ shell allows you to run applications (eg. to access your wallet, for VoIP and messaging / e-mail in protected mode, etc.) within the sandbox, directly at the OS level. SecureShield ™ uses an access model to regulate the access of applications to hardware system resources.

Author: deort
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Well, now everything has become, more or less, understandably, thanks)) Only I had another question: which hardware system resources will be accessed by the access rights model?

Author: dayasinfo
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The access rights model will regulate the access of applications to the resources of sensors, communications, peripherals and system processes. With the full list I advise you to read the technical documentation of the project.

Author: gavrosh
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: I would also like to add that in addition to regulating access rights at the SecureShield ™ level, you can further restrict access through a hardware switch on the device and two-step authentication via Authentication Manager.

Author: Liordav
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: So the main thing that stands out for security is the cold storage wallet, imagine a Trezor wallet built in your phone. Finney™ will have a physical toggle (switch) that will immediately turn off all unencrypted communications. Thanks to this mechanism the crypto wallet inside Finney™ will effectively be offline unless intentionally activated, functioning as a “cold wallet”. more than that FINNEY™ devices are multilayer cyber protected, from the hardware and low-level OS to the application layer. Acknowledging the dynamic nature of cyber threats, SIRIN LABS’ cybersecurity protection is developed on a behavioral-based and machine learning Intrusion Prevention System (IPS), for proactive cyber protection. see our integrated product from Zimperium here https://www.zimperium.com/zips-mobile-ips

Author: Liordav
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: The FINNEY is a special device branded by Sirin Labs, it will run Shield OS, our extension to Android and will be certified by Google, same as we did with Solarin. the estimated cost of the smartphone is 999$. you will be able to pre-order it with SRN tokens after the crowdsale. we have several motivations for the device and token economy - first, the token will be used to buys the device, so if the token price goes up you actually buy the device with less token that you may have bought in less than 999$. second, there is a pre-order discount. third, we plan to reward the community, every new device will get some amount of SRN token on the first activation of the device cold wallet. And the most important: we are pushing towards an open developer community where developers and device vendors adopt our OS and SDK and create more devices and apps that runs Shield OS and use the SRN token. these apps can implement P2P micropayments, resource sharing, and more. in addition, we will have few of the best d-apps in the market like status and stox adopt our SDK and come preloaded on FINNEY. these apps will enjoy one of the most important features of the SDK  - seamless token conversion between other tokens to there own token. here is Stox announcement about our cooperation: https://medium.com/@stoxhq/stox-and-sirin-labs-announce-partnership-3c52864b9175  for more details please visit our website https://www.sirinlabs.com/ and read the white paper https://www.sirinlabs.com/media/SIRINLABS_-_White_Paper.pdf

Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Very interesting project. I read about this earlier before the post, so I wasn't aware that the ICO hasn't been announced. A few questions:  1. What if you bought $999 of SRN tokens and then when the phone comes out, the tokens have dropped in value? Will you be forced to buy more SRN to buy the phone? Will this not encourage people to just wait for the phone to come out, and then buy SRN tokens with $999 and buy the phone? 2. The money will be credited daily to phone owners or SRN buyers?  Very interesting project, are you the representative for Sirin Labs?

Author: YonaTAK1
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Hi, I am a representative for SIRIN LABS, thanks for the questions.  1. We anticipate the value of the SRN token to increase significantly over the coming months up until the FINNEY' release. Of course, there is no guarantee that this will happen. The quantity of SRN needed to buy the phone will be determined by its market price. We think the price will increase for a number of reasons. The SRN token has multiple applications and powers the whole SIRIN LABS ecosystem, including usage in the Dapps store. We have an incredibly strong team (40+ people) and partners, and have already delivered a high quality product in the 'SOLARIN'. We believe FINNEY will connect the mainstream consumer to the blockchain economy and help enable mass adoption of cryptocurrency, FINNEY will be the bridge.  2. There will be an allocation of SRN tokens for the activation of your FINNEY cold wallet - there will be a daily pool of SRN tokens allocated for 'activation of cold wallets' that will be distributed between the number of wallets activated on that particular day.  Hope that helps!

Author: melmel7007
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: [/b] FINNEY™ by SIRIN LABS Secure Open Source Consumer Electronics for the Blockchain Era  START DATE: DECEMER 12, 2017 at 12:00PM GMT END DATE: DECEMBER 25, 2017 at 12:00PM GMT  SIRIN LABS' VISION To create a seamless bridge between blockchain technologies, apps and services and the mass market.   WHAT IS FINNEY™? The current generation of smart devices compromises on user security. The focus is overwhelmingly on user experience, at a huge cost in fraud and cybercrime. We believe the digital economy of the future cannot tolerate this trade-off: device architecture demands a paradigm shift that enables true security while maintaining excellent user experience.  FINNEY™ devices are the first cyber-protected, blockchain-enabled mobile phone and PC. They enjoy the functionality of Android™ OS, plus a suite of cybersecurity technologies, giving users safe, reliable access to the blockchain.  FINNEY™ devices form an independent blockchain network, a distributed ledger both scalable and lightweight, powered by IOTA’s Tangle technology and SIRIN LABS’ security ecosystem. FINNEY™ is free from centralized backbones and mining centers, capable of providing fast, fee-less and secure transactions.  FINNEY™ devices will run on SIRIN LABS’ open-source operating system, SIRIN OS™. This is designed to support inherent Blockchain applications, such as a crypto wallet, secure exchange access, encrypted communications, and a P2P resource sharing ecosystem for payment and apps, supported by the SRN token. The SRN is the FINNEY™ network’s default currency. Here are a few examples:  CONNECTIVITY Stay connected while traveling abroad, using P2P data connection sharing over FINNEY™ devices network  CPU Monetize FINNEY™ devices’ computer power while idle, sharing over the secure FINNEY™ network  POWER Running low on battery is solved, by trading battery power with another FINNEY™ user  DAY TO DAY Securely send and receive payments for services and products, using FINNEY™ fee-less transactions system  SIRIN LABS will partner with consumer electronics OEMs to promote the adoption of FINNEY™ architecture, the software platform, and the SRN currency. Both hardware and software platforms will be released as open source   The SIRIN LABS Token (SRN) The SIRIN LABS ecosystem is based on an open-source cryptographic token named SIRIN Token, whose symbol is SRN. The SRN cryptocurrency token is fractionally divisible, transferable and exchangeable. During the token sale, the SRN Token is implemented as an ERC-20 compatible token over the public Ethereum blockchain and will be converted to a coin on the IOTA network towards the launch.  SRN token will be available for usage and purchasing of SIRIN LABS existing products and services, as long with pre-order of future products.  Activity in the SIRIN LABS ecosystem is exclusively performed using the SRN token, making it an integral part of FINNEY™ devices use and economy.   FINNEY™ WEBSITE Website  FINNEY™ WHITEPAPER Whitepaper   FINNEY™ IN THE PRESS Techcrunch Endgadget Business Insider, and more.  Follow us on social media Facebook Instagram Medium Twitter   Watch Jason Silva, from the National Geographic, talk about FINNEY™ Vimeo YouTube   Join us on Telegram!

Author: Liordav
Title: [ANN] [ICO] SIRIN LABS ICO - Secure Blockchain Consumer Electronics
Body: Hi, I am Lior and I am a software engineer at Sirin Labs.  To Answer some of the questions you raised:  The main idea beyond a secure smartphone with a built-in wallet and a token is Shield OS.  Shield OS is Sirin Lab's open source extension framework to Android, our goal is that Shield OS will be adopted by more device manufacturers (FINNEY is a showcase) and reach the mass market.  Shield OS comes with SDK that gives device manufacturers and the developers community the power to build apps that make use of the decentralized world capabilities: Sirin decentralized fee less network, fast micropayments, cold wallet access, resource sharing services and the SRN token infrastructure.  Developers can develop apps that do micropayments for services like mobile data, local mobile data instead of roaming, wifi, also services that are not related to mobile resource share, like: location-based advertisement in exchange to SRNs.  mine while idle - this is actually an implementation suggestion, a developer can create an app that makes use of the Shield OS SDK to share computing resources while idle in exchange for SRNs  power - yes, the example we gave about power was sharing smartphone battery power, this will require a cable connection between the devices, and again its one example of using the SDK capabilities.   I will be happy to answer more questions on our technical aspects.   Thank you!
